com.vmware.esx.settings.clusters.configuration

Class HostResult

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.vmware.esx.settings.clusters.configuration.HostResult
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    com.vmware.vapi.bindings.StaticStructure, com.vmware.vapi.bindings.Structure, java.io.Serializable

    public final class HostResult
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable, com.vmware.vapi.bindings.StaticStructure
    This HostResult class contains properties that describe the result of the check compliance operation on an ESXi host. This class was added in vSphere API 8.0.1.0.

    • Method Detail

      • getHostStatus

        public HostStatus getHostStatus()
        This field represents the status of the check compliance operation. If status is OK, the result of operation can be retrived from {#HostCompliance} {#Summary} field will summarize the status of the operation and if applicable, the specific error that occured. Additionally, {#ValidationError} is populated if the operation fails due to host validation errors in desired document. This property was added in vSphere API 8.0.1.0.
        Returns:
        The current value of the property.

      • getErrors

        public java.util.List<ValidationError> getErrors()

        Returns:
        The current value of the property.

        Parameters:

      • getHostCompliance

        public HostCompliance getHostCompliance()
        This field provides compliance results for the host if the operation successfully completed on the host. That is, this field is populated only if HostStatus is OK. This property was added in vSphere API 8.0.1.0. This field is null if check compliance could not be completed on the host.
        Returns:
        The current value of the property.

      • setHostCompliance

        Parameters:
        hostCompliance - New value for the property.
